<th colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; font-size:125%; font-weight:bold;">Animal rights</th>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Shanghai-monkey.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Shanghai-monkey.jpg" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/bd/Shanghai-monkey.jpg/160px-Shanghai-monkey.jpg" width="160" height="260" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/bd/Shanghai-monkey.jpg/240px-Shanghai-monkey.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/bd/Shanghai-monkey.jpg/320px-Shanghai-monkey.jpg 2x" /></a><br />
<span style="">Many animal rights advocates propose that animals be viewed as <a href="Person" title="Person">persons</a>, not property.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></span></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Description</th>
<td class="" style="">Nonhuman animals have interests, and those interests ought not to be discriminated against on the basis of <a href="Speciesism" title="Speciesism">species membership alone</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
